1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

This paper examines the modern phenomenon of Prestige Physics Without Physics (PPWP) — a growing intellectual industry in which individuals attempt to position themselves as revolutionary scientific figures while operating largely outside the constraints of mathematics, experimental validation, or institutional peer review.

The Institute’s central claim is as follows:

The modern zero-point energy and aether revival movements are not primarily scientific movements. They are status movements.

These movements operate within what we designate the Attention Economy of Genius (AEG), in which the primary scarce resource is not energy, funding, or experimental evidence, but recognition as a misunderstood revolutionary.

The paper further concludes that many participants are not attempting to solve the energy crisis, but rather attempting to solve the personal legacy problem: how to become Einstein without doing Einstein’s work.

