2. THE EINSTEIN MISUNDERSTANDING

2.1 The Einstein Myth vs The Einstein Method

The Institute has identified a critical historical misinterpretation known as the Einstein Myth Error (EME).

Einstein Myth	Einstein Reality
Lone genius	Worked within physics community
Ignored by establishment	Published in leading journals
Pure thought	Math + thought experiments
Rebels against physics	Extended physics
Intuition only	Mathematical consistency
Wanted fame	Wanted correct equations

But the most important characteristic, as identified by the Institute, was:

Einstein’s primary trait was not intelligence. It was his inability to lie to himself about whether the math worked.

This trait is formally defined as Internal Intellectual Honesty (IIH), and the Institute considers it the single most important variable in scientific discovery.

