4. THE AUTHORITY LIST ARGUMENT

A common argument structure observed in these communities is the Institution List Substitution Fallacy (ILSF):

Argument Form:
	•	NASA looked at it
	•	CIA funded something
	•	A patent exists
	•	Therefore it works

This is logically equivalent to the following:

Claim	Reality
Studied	Not validated
Funded	Not confirmed
Patented	Not proven
Investigated	Not real
Classified	Not working
Secret	Not functional

The Institute reminds readers of the First Rule of Reality:

If it worked, it would be used.

Not hidden.
Not teased on Twitter.
Used.

Energy technology that works is not a podcast topic.
It is an infrastructure industry.

