8. THE CORE PSYCHOLOGICAL DRIVER

The Institute identifies the primary driver not as money, science, or engineering, but identity.

This phenomenon is defined as Einstein Identity Syndrome (EIS):

The desire to be the person who was right when everyone else was wrong is stronger than the desire to be correct.

This leads to the most dangerous cognitive state in research:

Non-Falsifiable Self-Esteem (NFSE) — a condition in which every failed experiment becomes proof of suppression rather than proof of being wrong.

Real science progresses by killing its own ideas.
Pseudoscience progresses by protecting its ideas from death.

