9. CONCLUSION

The Institute concludes the following:
	•	The energy problem is an engineering problem, not a Twitter problem.
	•	Physics is constrained by mathematics, not optimism.
	•	Listing institutions is not evidence.
	•	Patents are not proof.
	•	Being ignored is not proof of genius.
	•	Being ridiculed is not proof of correctness.
	•	Using the word “quantum” is not a theory.
	•	Using the word “classified” is not data.
	•	If you cannot build it, you do not have an energy technology.
	•	If you cannot write the equations, you do not have a physics theory.
	•	And most importantly:

You cannot be a revolutionary scientist if you are not brutally honest about when you are wrong.

Einstein changed physics because he followed the math even when it contradicted him.
These movements attempt to change physics by ignoring the math when it contradicts them.

These are not the same process.

